white.description: Base white for theme tokens and general purposes.

Mini Chip.description: For the notifications that are in the navigation

subtle-2x.description: For light surface contrasts, such as in My List row items where there is surface on surface, usually one is white over the subtle 2x.

placeholder.description: For text placeholders inside fileds. Mostly for search fields. Can also apeear in a few disabled state elements, like text.

subtle-2x.description: For darker items like icons in buttons with or without text. Also, used in secondary level descriptive text that needs a subtle contrast against titles.

subtle-3x.description: For contrast against text. For icons fills/borders. It's also used coupled with a list item text. See Inputs Dropdown for examples.

strong.description: For important text instances colors, list items, table cell texts,  in resting state.

strongest.description: For important text instances colors, list items, table cell texts, table headers, titles, in hover and selected states.

emphasis-2x.description: Since emphasis is a strong color, the 2x should be stronger then its predecessor.

hover.description: Hover style for CTAs in error messages. Also used in higher level titles for contrast.

subtle.description: For cta background and success feedback surfaces.

subtle-2x.description: For cta background and success feedback surfaces that need more contract by still should be subtle.

on-success-mono.description: To achieve a monochromatic look. This dark success works on sutble and subtle--2x surfaces.

default.description: Border used mostly for gray buttons.

strong-2x.description: For icons that are on gray surfaces, so contrast has the correct accessability.

subtle-1x.description: Border used mostly for dividers of sections and tables.

subtle-2x.description: Can also be a fill for stepper items or applied to other items to keep tokens' list smaller.

alert-1.description: For positive incentive alerts. Great for upgrading reminders to evoke good feelings instead of fear.

focused.description: Similar to effects token theme/shadow/Focused/default, this is for strokes on focused state items that were initially created with a border instead of the shadow effect.

subtle-2x.description: For light surface contrasts, such as in My List row items where there is surface on surface, usually one is white over the subtle 2x.

field.description: Dark color for fields to have a slight contracts against other surfaces. In same cases, can be used in tooltips.

placeholder.description: For text placeholders inside fileds. Mostly for search fields.

subtle-3x.description: For contrast against text. For icons fills/borders. It's also used coupled with a list item text. See Inputs Dropdown for examples.

strong.description: For text of inputs and buttons in resting state.

subtle-2x.description: One degree ligher then subtle. Usually for component's surface, like alerts or items that need to contrast with the brand-persian-blue and brand-persian-blue-dark.

hover.description: Hover style for CTAs in error messages.

subtle.description: For cta background and success feedback surfaces.

subtle-2x.description: For cta background and success feedback surfaces that need more contract by still should be subtle.

on-success-mono.description: To achieve a monochromatic look. This dark success works on sutble and subtle--2x surfaces.

default.description: Border used mostly for gray buttons.

strong-2x.description: For icons that are on gray surfaces, so contrast has the correct accessability.

subtle-1x.description: Border used mostly for dividers of sections and tables. Can also be used for disabled borders on all items. Corresponding disabled token for surfaces is theme/fg/disabled.

alert-1.description: For positive incentive alerts. Great for upgrading reminders to evoke good feelings instead of fear.

disabled.description: For disabled borders on all items. For disabled fill use the corresponding disabled token for surfaces is theme/fg/disabled.

focused.description: Similar to effects token theme/shadow/Focused/default, this is for strokes on focused state items that were initially created with a border instead of the shadow effect.
